  "prompt": "How do I convert Indian grading system's pointer, CGPA (out of 10) , into the GPA of American grading system?",
  "response": "To convert the Indian CGPA (Cumulative Grade Point Average) to the American GPA system, you'll need to follow these steps:\n\n1. Indian CGPA is typically on a 10-point scale, while American GPA is usually on a 4-point scale.\n\n2. Basic conversion formula:\n   American GPA = (Indian CGPA \u00f7 10) \u00d7 4\n\nExample:\n- If your Indian CGPA is 7.5\n- Conversion: (7.5 \u00f7 10) \u00d7 4 = 3.0 American GPA\n\nAdditional notes:\n- This is a straightforward linear conversion\n- Some universities might have slight variations\n- For precise conversion, check with specific university requirements\n- Many international credential evaluation services can help with official conversions\n\nQuick reference:\n- 10.0 Indian CGPA = 4.0 American GPA\n- 9.0 Indian CGPA = 3.6 American GPA\n- 8.0 Indian CGPA = 3.2 American GPA\n- 7.0 Indian CGPA = 2.8 American GPA\n- 6.0 Indian CGPA = 2.4 American GPA\n\nAlways verify with the specific institution you're applying to.",
